<br>
VF is a combo based fighter. Like DOA is. You attack your opponent with combos/strings, and to master the game you have to learn which combos are right for the opponent you are playing. So people who like to do combos are attracted to games like VF and DOA.<br>
<br>
Tekken's system however is more of a &quot;dynamic&quot; styled fighting. You dont use long strings to attack your opponent, instead you have to mix things up with a quick number of hits and then wait for your opponent to counter attack, or go into another short string to hopefully counter attack their own counter attack. The goal of every good player is to hopefully get them into the air so they can do juggle combos. Which are Tekken's true &quot;combos&quot; even though they arent like combos you would see in another game. Because its not a very combo friendly game, newbies have a hard time getting into it and will describe the controls as &quot;stiff.&quot; While a newbie vs a newbie is a good match, a newbie vs someone who knows how Tekken works will get humiliated.<br>
___________<br>
<br>
